item.title: What are java files?
item.dc:creator: @Greeny Greeny
item.description:
@Greeny wrote:

[quote="[-J O H N-"]link=topic=218906.msg1900336#msg1900336 date=1196086288]
Java files are used to created class files. Your server should run off class Files… When you compile it translates your java coding into a new language and that allows what you added to work if it was added successfully. If you decompiled a class file successfully you’d get what you typed in your java files to start with. Thats the best I can explain :[/quote]

Good try but it’s wrong, it’s not coded into a new language, it’s still Java it’s just as something the JVM can interpret, ie bytecode. When you decompile the code is actually slightly different, because during compilation things are added, and stuff like comments are removed.
